CatDescriptText: Portion of article by John Clark, published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 16, 1957, pg. B4 reads: "Alcorn Meade, GOP National Chairman, Says, 'Party Follows Abe Lincoln's Creed' - More than 900 Lincoln Day dinner guests heard the new chairman of the Republican National Committee, H. Meade Alcorn say that the dynamic direction of Abraham Lincoln's philosophy is the foundation of the Eisenhower policy..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five women, including one wearing dark dress and tiara, and four men, seated around table in Penn Sheraton hotel for Lincoln Day dinner
